						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab (No. 2) built into east wall of the central shrine of Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 15th century.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers to a gift of land, money and oil, probably made to a god, the details of which are all lost. It refers to god Mahāliṅga.</p>						

						</summary>
